**No sentinel error for permanent job failure**

When a Job has permanently failed, `RunJob` returns an opaque `fmt.Errorf` string. Callers (reconcilers) cannot distinguish this permanent-failure case from transient failures (network errors, etcd timeouts, etc.) without fragile string-matching. As a result, the default Kubernetes controller-runtime error path will requeue the reconcile with exponential backoff — causing the reconciler to produce the same error on every retry until a human manually deletes the failed Job.

Consider exporting a sentinel error variable so callers can use `errors.Is` to detect and handle the permanent-failure case explicitly (e.g., stop requeueing, emit an event, set a condition on the owner):

```go
// ErrJobFailed is returned by RunJob when the Job has exceeded its backoffLimit
// and will not be retried automatically.
var ErrJobFailed = errors.New("job has permanently failed")

// ...

if IsJobFailed(existing) {
    return false, fmt.Errorf("%w: %s/%s", ErrJobFailed, existing.Namespace, existing.Name)
}
```

Reconcilers can then do:

```go
if errors.Is(err, job.ErrJobFailed) {
    // emit event, set Failed condition, do not requeue
    return ctrl.Result{}, nil
}
return ctrl.Result{}, err
```

